<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="365" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[809,1421,245,439]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">
This species was previously recorded by Verschuren (1977) and Wolton 
<emphasis box="[1171,1231,278,304]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">et al</emphasis>
. (1982) at Mt 
<collectingRegion box="[809,889,312,338]" country="Liberia" name="Nimba" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Nimba</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[930,1015,312,338]" name="Liberia" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Liberia</collectingCountry>
and by 
<bibRefCitation author="FAHR, J. &amp; B. A. DJOSSA &amp; H. VIERHAUS" box="[1115,1326,312,338]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" pagination="245 - 247" refId="ref13222" refString="FAHR, J., B. A. DJOSSA, and H. VIERHAUS. 2006. Rapid assessment of bats (Chiroptera) in Dere, Diecke and Mt. Bero classified forests, southeastern Guinea; including a review of the distribution of bats in Guinee Forestiere. Pp. 168 - 180, 245 - 247, in A rapid biological assessment of three classified forests in Southeastern Guinea (H. E. WRIGHT, J. MCCULLOUGH, L. E. ALONSO, and M. S. DIALLO, eds.). Conservation International, RAP Bulletin of Biological Assessment, Washington, D. C., 40, 248 pp." type="book chapter" year="2006">
Fahr 
<emphasis box="[1178,1231,312,338]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">et al</emphasis>
. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
in 
<collectingCountry name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Guinea</collectingCountry>
. During this study, it was recorded at two forested sites on the Liberian side between 
<quantity box="[1294,1370,379,405]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" unit="m" value="480.0">480 m</quantity>
and 
<quantity box="[809,884,413,439]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" unit="m" value="730.0">730 m</quantity>
a.s.l.
</paragraph>
